title.narrative: Output 3.1. By 2020, an integrated national child protection system that prevents and responds to violence, exploitation, abuse, discrimination and neglect and ensures the care of vulnerable children.

description.narrative: The National Child Policy was approved by Cabinet. MGLSD and UBOS provided support supervision and mentorship to eight-learning districts on the use of data for planning and budgeting and implementation of the harmonized coordination mechanism to prevent VAC/W. 18,431,702 (9,173,121 male, 9,258,581 female) 15-17 years old persons received messages from a media campaign on VAC and harmful practices on radio, television and social media platforms. 3,989 para-social workers in 15 districts were mobilized and empowered to deliver coordinated VAC prevention and harmful practices interventions. The midterm evaluation of the national strategy to end child marriage and teenage was finalized. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:17/08/2020
